### Capstone — URL shortener

@base = http://localhost:3006
@me = alice

### Meta
GET {{base}}/
GET {{base}}/_stats

### 1) Create a short URL (rate-limit: 20 / min / ip)
POST {{base}}/shorten
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{me}}

{
  "target": "https://nodejs.org/"
}

### 2) Grab the code from step 1 and set it here:
@code = REPLACE_ME_WITH_CODE_FROM_STEP_1

### 3) Public redirect — first call is a cache miss, subsequent calls are hits
GET {{base}}/{{code}}

### 4) Peek at cache
GET {{base}}/_stats

### 5) My URLs
GET {{base}}/me/urls
x-user-id: {{me}}

### 6) Analytics (needs at least a few redirects first)
GET {{base}}/analytics/{{code}}
x-user-id: {{me}}

### 7) Bad target
POST {{base}}/shorten
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: {{me}}

{ "target": "not-a-url" }

### 8) 404 — negative cache kicks in on the second attempt
GET {{base}}/nope123

### 9) Delete
DELETE {{base}}/{{code}}
x-user-id: {{me}}

### 10) Access someone else's code
POST {{base}}/shorten
Content-Type: application/json
x-user-id: bob

{ "target": "https://redis.io/" }

### … then try to view its analytics as alice — should be 403
GET {{base}}/analytics/CODE_OWNED_BY_BOB
x-user-id: alice
